.TH B4MARKDOWN 1 "March 2026" "AutoReadme" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
b4markdown \- Markdown preprocessor with syntax highlighting and file inclusion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B b4markdown
[\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B b4markdown
is a preprocessor for Markdown that adds syntax highlighting markup and file inclusion capabilities before passing content to markdown_py.
.PP
Features:
.IP \(bu 2
Syntax highlighting with color markers (@- gray, @+ cyan, @g green, @b blue, @p purple, @y yellow, @r red, @o orange)
.IP \(bu 2
Form feed markers (@@) for page breaks
.IP \(bu 2
File inclusion with #include directive
.IP \(bu 2
Mermaid diagram support with automatic script inclusion
.IP \(bu 2
Markdown comment stripping
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B FILE
Input file to process. If not specified, reads from standard input.
.SH SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
Lines beginning with color markers are converted to HTML mark elements:
.PP
.nf
@- Text in gray
@g Text in green
@@ Page break
.fi
.SH FILE INCLUSION
Include other files with:
.PP
.nf
#include filename.md
.fi
.SH MERMAID DIAGRAMS
Mermaid code blocks are automatically enhanced with the Mermaid.js library.
.SH OUTPUT
HTML output from markdown_py with additional markup for highlighting and diagrams.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Process a file:
.B b4markdown document.md
.TP
Process from stdin:
.B cat document.md | b4markdown
.TP
Use in pipeline:
.B generate_html uses b4markdown internally
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Requires markdown_py with extra extensions for full functionality.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR generate_html (1),
.BR markdown_py (1),
.BR autoreadme (1)
.SH AUTHOR
AutoReadme project